<br>
Obviously would require the use of Pillar of Frost.  <br>
<br>
Obviously, wyverns resist cold-based spells a lot.  Not ALL the time, but a lot.  50% at least.  I tried to kite one around with it to test, it looked like it was going to be REALLY close so I went ahead and finished it off with Draught rather than risk it.  <br>
<br>
I don't have my temp flux staff yet.  Does the debuff effect of this staff make THAT much difference that quadding these wyverns at 51 with PoFrost actually becomes feasible?<br>
<br>
Next question, is it like Jboots, where you can keep running and click them, and the effect is instantaneous?  Or do you have to stop and click and wait a couple seconds, while trailing other not-snared-yet wyverns behind you?<br>
